performers.name: Nikolas Martell
performers.bio: Nikolas Martell is a professional performing artist, specializing in spoken word. He is a national slam poetry champion, slam poetry coach, and producer of the OUTspoken! Presents monthly queer open mic and cabaret series.

performers.name: Mahmoud Hakima
performers.bio: Mahmoud Hakima is a Twin Cities storyteller. He created and performed the MN Fringe solo hits, "Two Bowls  of Cereal and Some Bacon" and "Can Michael Come Out and Play?"
